===Noun===
'''love''' (''uncountable and countable''; ''plural'' '''[[loves]]''')
# (''uncountable'') An intense feeling of [[affection]] towards another.
# (''uncountable'') An initimate sexual interest or fascination towards something or someone.
# (''uncountable'') [[romantic|Romantic]] [[feeling]]s.
# (''uncountable'') An underlying sense of unity or sameness.
# (''countable'') The subject of one's romantic interest.
# (''countable'') A [[darling]] or [[sweetheart]].
# (''colloquial'') A term of address, regardless of feelings.
#:''Hello '''love''', how can I help you?''
# (''in tennis'') Zero. (from French l'oeuf - the egg, referring to the shape of zero)
# One's desire that another be happy.

